een ambitious global health goals and the local realities. Interrogating how culture and technical problems are framed in international health interventions, Rudrum reveals that the objectifying and colonizing premises on which interventions are based often result in the negative consequences in local healthcare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aChildbirthzUgandazAmuru District. 0aMaternal health serviceszUgandazAmuru District. 0aMedical assistancezUgandazAmuru District. 0aPublic healthxInternational cooperation. 0aWar and societyzUgandazAmuru District. 0aWorld health. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aAcholi.  aUganda.  acritical health studies.  aglobal health.  ainstitutional ethnography.  amaternity care.  awomen’s health.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073922040uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753042640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487530426423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487530426/original  a978-3-11-073922-0  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075412-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EB